ically from Persia to the Caucasus and from there to Berlin today, and thematically the volume offers an impressive variety of subjects from history, philology, literature and cultural studies to the philosophy of law, sociology and politics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aTurkish languagexHistory. 0aTurkish literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aOsmanisches Reich /Geschichte. 4aOsmanisches Reich /Gesellschaft, Sozialwissenschaften. 4aTürkei /Geschichte. 4aTürkei /Gesellschaft, Sozialwissenschaften. 7aHISTORY / Civilization.2bisacsh  aOttoman Empire (History, Society, Social Studies).  aTurkish Empire (History, Society, Social Studies).1 aAdatepe, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCzygan, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaroqhi, Suraiya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenz, Hendrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenz, Hendrik, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFinke, Detlev, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlemming, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGropp, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöbenli, Mediha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohanson, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarakaşoğlu, Yasemin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnüppel, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreiser, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaut, Jens Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc